                            <comment id="404200" author="adilger" created="Fri, 16 Feb 2024 16:03:46 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;All of these failures in the past 4 weeks are on the netlink patches, so it appears to be a regression in the patches themselves and should not be considered a separate bug. It looks like the common factor is patch &lt;a href=&quot;https://review.whamcloud.com/53889&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://review.whamcloud.com/53889&lt;/a&gt; &quot;&lt;tt&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-9680&quot; title=&quot;Improve the user land to kernel space interface for lustre&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-9680&quot;&gt;LU-9680&lt;/a&gt; utils: fix nested attribute handling in liblnetconfig&lt;/tt&gt;&quot;.&lt;/p&gt;


&lt;p&gt;This can be easily searched by clicking the &quot;&lt;tt&gt;55b&lt;/tt&gt;&quot; link in the Maloo test results page, then expanding the time window to 4 weeks:&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;https://testing.whamcloud.com/search?horizon=2332800&amp;amp;status%5B%5D=TIMEOUT&amp;amp;test_set_script_id=f9516376-32bc-11e0-aaee-52540025f9ae&amp;amp;sub_test_script_id=fc8a3098-d7ee-484b-97e4-dec8cb55b491&amp;amp;source=sub_tests#redirect&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://testing.whamcloud.com/search?horizon=2332800&amp;amp;status%5B%5D=TIMEOUT&amp;amp;test_set_script_id=f9516376-32bc-11e0-aaee-52540025f9ae&amp;amp;sub_test_script_id=fc8a3098-d7ee-484b-97e4-dec8cb55b491&amp;amp;source=sub_tests#redirect&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
